radiographic_examinations.findings: Small left pleural effusion with overlying atelectasis. The right lung is clear except for some minimal atelectasis at the base. A small punctate hypodense lesion within segment II of the liver, likely a cyst. Hypodensity adjacent to the falciform ligament suggesting focal fatty infiltration. Significant peripancreatic stranding and small amounts of fluid consistent with pancreatitis. No pancreatic ductal dilatation, heterogeneous pancreatic head with no definite signs of necrosis. Moderate amount of free fluid within the pelvis.
